            <div type="commentary">
                <p><!--commented out pending revision-->
          <!--2 joining frr. from a long inscr; NB Mommsen considered this and the two further frr. (his ii-iii) listed under IMusCat 23 as all belonging to the same and many others have followed incl Manganaro (1989); but Korhonen and Manganaro 1959 consider them separate, albeit from the same context; note another fragment found in via Dusmet in 1958 is generally agreed to be another text again, and not located in the Museo civico by Korhonen . Mention of several official positions; letter of Iulius Paternus to M. Aurelius and Lucius Verus, recording his building activities, in the face of some civic resistance to the expense; perhaps involved in harbour works. In general, see Manganaro and Korhonen. Important text for municipal activity. Whether Iulius a curator rei publicae or curator operis is unclear. NB cf. Korhonen, IMusCat 23 also. Cf. also CIL XIV.3593 for a curator in the C3 AD.-->
                </p>
